title: Live coverage: SpaceX to launch 24 Starlink satellites on Falcon 9 rocket from Cape Canaveral
summary: The Starlink 6-66 mission comes near the end of a week during which SpaceX launched three Falcon 9 rockets in less than 20 hours and a Starship rocket. Liftoff from pad 40 at Cape Canaveral Space Force Station is set for 11:07 a.m. EST (1607 UTC).

title: Launch Roundup: Falcon 9 launches continue, Rocket Lab to launch two Electrons, Russia to fly to ISS
summary: Following the sixth flight of SpaceX’s Starship on Tuesday, four additional orbital launches are planned worldwide. Rocket Lab will launch an experimental hypersonic testbed payload using a modified Electron from Wallops. What’s more, a second Electron will launch a batch of nanosatellites into low-Earth orbit from New Zealand.

title: Launch Roundup: Falcon 9 launches customer payloads, China fly resupply mission to Tiangong
summary: While SpaceX is preparing to fly Starship on its sixth integrated test flight this week, the company flew one satellite and plans to fly two more to geostationary transfer orbit this week. Koreasat 6A has flown while Optus-X and GSAT-20 are also scheduled to fly. Meanwhile, four Starlink missions were scheduled to fly this week, with three already having flown. Finally Starship Flight 6 will round out the launch week.
